dataIdInfo.idAbs: Vector file of public/private streets and ferry crossings compiled from orthoimagery and other sources. Attributed with street names and route numbers.
dataIdInfo.idPurp: A vector street layer suitable for use in a GIS and can be made available to the general public. The file has had addressing and routing attributes removed.

LegConsts.othConsts: Access constraints: This GIS Data and derivative products are copyright protected and have been licensed to OCS. Under its license, OCS has the right to make the GIS Data and derivative products available to the general public.

Consts.useLimit: This GIS Data and derivative products may be used for any lawful purpose. Commercial use of this data requires prior approval from the NYS Office of Cyber Security.

LegConsts.othConsts: Use constraints: This GIS Data and derivative products may be used for any lawful purpose. Commercial use of this data requires prior approval from the NYS Office of Cyber Security.

dataIdInfo.suppInfo: This data was created as part of the Accident Location Information System (ALIS) project. A major component of the ALIS Project was the creation of up-to-date statewide Geographic Information System (GIS) files.
dataIdInfo.envirDesc: Microsoft Windows XP Version 5.1 (Build 2600) Service Pack 3; ESRI ArcGIS 10.0.0.2414

dqReport.measDesc: The New York State Office of Cyber Security makes no claims to the accuracy of the information in this file.

prcStep.stepDesc: A Product and Process Description (PPD) document is available for download on the NYS GIS Clearinghouse at: http://www.gis.ny.gov/gisdata/inventories/details.cfm?DSID=932 The PPD document describes the various data elements contained in this file and their requirements. For each data "layer" or "object, it will describe the relevant processes and procedures used to make this file._____New Since Original Build: Hyphens have been removed from the Queens style addressed roads. In cases where leading zero(es) existed on a house number, one leading zero was removed.

dataSource.srcDesc: A Source Usage Document (SUD) spreadsheet is available for download on the NYS GIS Clearinghouse at: http://www.gis.ny.gov/gisdata/inventories/details.cfm?DSID=932 The SUD spreadsheet identifies by individual county what data was provided and how such GIS data was used to build the layer.

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.
